---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import Nav from "../../components/Nav.astro";
import Footer from "../../components/Footer.astro";
const currentPath = "/blog/";
---

<BaseLayout title="Blog — Packaging Insights | Yuanmei Printing" description="Expert insights on custom packaging, box manufacturing, material selection, and design trends for global brands." lang="en" currentPath={currentPath}>
<Nav lang="en" currentPath={currentPath} />

<main class="page">
<section class="page-hero"><div class="container"><h1>Packaging Insights</h1><p>Expert guides, tips, and trends in custom packaging</p></div></section>
<section class="section section-alt">
<div class="container">
<div class="blog-grid">
{[{title:"How to Choose the Right Paper Stock for Your Packaging",date:"June 2026",desc:"Paper choice defines your packaging. Grey board (1200gsm) is ideal for rigid luxury boxes — it's thick, durable, and holds embossing beautifully. Coated art paper gives a glossy, vibrant surface for high-end retail. Kraft paper offers a natural, eco-friendly feel popular with organic brands. For food packaging, always specify food-grade materials compliant with FDA or EU standards. Not sure? Send us your product and we'll recommend the best stock. Our MOQ starts at just 50 pieces per design, so testing is low-risk."},{title:"5 Box Finishes That Elevate Your Brand",date:"May 2026",desc:"Finishes turn a plain box into a brand statement. Hot foil stamping adds metallic luxury — gold, silver, or holographic. Spot UV creates a glossy highlight on specific areas, perfect for logos. Matte lamination gives a smooth, premium feel that resists fingerprints. Embossing raises your design for a tactile 3D effect. Soft touch coating feels velvety — customers can't stop touching it. Combine two finishes for maximum impact: foil + emboss is a classic. All five finishes are available in-house at Yuanmei, keeping your costs down and turnaround fast."},{title:"The Complete Guide to Packaging MOQ: What Startups Need to Know",date:"April 2026",desc:"MOQ (Minimum Order Quantity) exists because setup costs are the same whether you order 50 or 5,000 boxes. At Yuanmei, we keep MOQ low — 50 pieces per design — because we know startups and small brands need flexibility. Larger orders always get better unit pricing, but you don't need to order thousands to get started. Our advice: order 50-100 for your first batch, test the market, then scale. We also keep your dieline on file, so reorders are faster and cheaper. No hidden fees, no minimum spend."},{title:"DDP Shipping Explained: Getting Your Boxes from China to Your Door",date:"March 2026",desc:"DDP (Delivered Duty Paid) means we handle everything — freight, customs clearance, duties, and taxes — and deliver directly to your address. You pay one price and your boxes arrive at your door. This is the preferred method for our international clients because it eliminates surprises: no unexpected customs bills, no logistics headaches. We ship to 40+ countries via sea freight (economical for large orders) or air freight (7-10 days for urgent needs). Your account manager tracks every shipment and updates you at each stage."},{title:"Sustainable Packaging: Options for Eco-Conscious Brands",date:"February 2026",desc:"Sustainability in packaging doesn't mean compromising on quality. We offer FSC-certified paper — sourced from responsibly managed forests. Soy-based inks replace petroleum-based alternatives with no loss in print quality. Water-based coatings are biodegradable alternatives to plastic lamination. Kraft paper boxes with minimal printing are naturally recyclable and compostable. For luxury brands, we can combine eco-materials with premium finishes: an FSC-certified rigid box with foil stamping still makes a statement. Ask us about our green packaging options — we'll help you balance sustainability with brand impact."},{title:"Die-Cut vs. Standard Boxes: Which Is Right for Your Product?",date:"January 2026",desc:"Standard boxes (straight tuck, reverse tuck, mailer) are fast, affordable, and perfect for most products. Die-cut boxes give you complete freedom — custom shapes, windows, cutouts, unique unboxing experiences. The trade-off? Die-cut requires a custom mold (one-time cost, typically $50-150) and adds 2-3 days to production. For subscription boxes or premium retail packaging, die-cut is worth it. For simple shipping boxes, standard is fine. Not sure? We can produce a sample of each so you can compare before committing to a full production run."}].map((post) => (
<article class="blog-card"><h3>{post.title}</h3><span class="blog-date">{post.date}</span><p>{post.desc}</p></article>
))}
</div>
</div>
</section>
</main>
<Footer lang="en"/>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
.page{background:#0a0a0f;color:#e0dce8}
.page-hero{padding:140px 0 64px;background:linear-gradient(135deg,var(--purple-bg),#2D1250);color:var(--white);text-align:center}
.page-hero h1{font-family:var(--font-display);font-size:clamp(36px,6vw,56px);font-weight:800;margin-bottom:12px}
.page-hero p{font-size:17px;color:#94a3b8}
.section{padding:80px 0}
.section-alt{background:#110d1a}
.container{max-width:1100px;margin:0 auto;padding:0 24px}
.blog-grid{display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(auto-fit,minmax(320px,1fr));gap:24px}
.blog-card{background:rgba(255,255,255,0.02);border:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.06);border-radius:12px;padding:28px;transition:border-color .2s}
.blog-card:hover{border-color:var(--purple-light)}
.blog-card h3{font-size:18px;font-weight:700;color:#e0dce8;margin-bottom:8px;line-height:1.4}
.blog-date{font-size:12px;color:var(--purple-light);letter-spacing:1px;text-transform:uppercase;display:block;margin-bottom:12px}
.blog-card p{font-size:14px;color:#9ca3af;line-height:1.7}
</style>
